00:03:42.120 --> 00:03:44.720
It used to be, okay, so what you're going to do

00:03:44.820 --> 00:03:48.560
is you're going to write a requirements.txt file

00:03:48.690 --> 00:03:50.280
and then you set your versions explicitly.

00:03:50.660 --> 00:03:56.180
And that, for many people, only addressed the primary dependencies, not the transitive

00:03:56.880 --> 00:03:58.080
dependency, you know, right?

00:03:58.140 --> 00:04:00.760
They might pin Flask, but did they depend Vexo?

00:04:01.080 --> 00:04:01.500
I don't know.

00:04:01.920 --> 00:04:02.580
