00:04:18.799 --> 00:04:21.380
I am loving that workflow these days.

00:04:22.620 --> 00:04:24.980
Yeah, that's what I've switched all the projects themselves to.

00:04:25.010 --> 00:04:28.220
So if you go look at Flask or Xoic or any of those,

00:04:29.740 --> 00:04:33.120
we have a requirements folder with different environment files

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:35.800
that say, here are our direct dependencies,

00:04:35.990 --> 00:04:38.560
and then we compile those into fully locked dependencies,

00:04:38.850 --> 00:04:40.360
and all our tests run off of those.

00:04:40.580 --> 00:04:44.380
Our build and publish workflow runs off of those.

00:04:45.860 --> 00:04:47.100
So it's not quite the same,

00:04:47.160 --> 00:04:48.980
because those are our development dependencies

00:04:49.180 --> 00:04:50.400
instead of our runtime dependencies.

00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:57.520
