00:13:52.680 --> 00:13:54.960
Pallets is an open source organization.

00:13:55.310 --> 00:14:02.320
So we're not a company, but we do have like a team of volunteer open source maintainers.

00:14:03.340 --> 00:14:10.520
who volunteer their free time to work on flask and the libraries that make up flask that was kind of

00:14:10.640 --> 00:14:17.540
its purpose when it was created was hey flask has these set of libraries um arvin the original author

00:14:17.740 --> 00:14:24.300
of them was uh not as involved in them anymore and like the community he wanted the community to be

00:14:24.420 --> 00:14:28.039
more involved in them so he created this organization this was right around when i was becoming maintainer

00:14:28.060 --> 00:14:29.060
or two eight years ago.

00:14:31.520 --> 00:14:33.440
And so it's kind of the organization

00:14:33.680 --> 00:14:39.080
that holds those projects and the team that kind of maintains

00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:41.600
and sets policies and that sort of thing.

00:14:42.600 --> 00:14:46.380
So Flask is the most popular library

00:14:46.440 --> 00:14:48.900
that everybody heard of, followed by Jinja and Click.

00:14:49.900 --> 00:14:53.200
But then we also have Verksoeg, which is the lower level stuff

00:14:53.340 --> 00:14:53.960
below Flask.

00:14:54.140 --> 00:14:55.879
And then Markup Safe and It's Dangerous

00:14:55.900 --> 00:14:59.240
or two little helper libraries for those things.

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:01.800
And then now we've also got Cort,

00:15:02.320 --> 00:15:04.980
which is the async version of Flask.

00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:07.980
And that's an official palettes project now,

00:15:08.020 --> 00:15:11.540
even though it started as just kind of a separate thing.

00:15:12.160 --> 00:15:14.920
Yeah, that was an outside thing that Philip Jones worked on.

00:15:14.940 --> 00:15:19.820
And now it's coming closer and closer to being official.

00:15:20.780 --> 00:15:21.180
Yeah.

00:15:23.040 --> 00:15:25.280
And we're doing a lot of work on that

00:15:26.620 --> 00:15:30.540
to try to unify Flask and Quart as much as possible.

00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:33.860
So behind the scenes, they're sharing a lot more code now.

00:15:35.780 --> 00:15:39.660
Quart-- like VaricsOg is all the low-level request response

00:15:40.140 --> 00:15:41.480
handling for the Flask uses.

00:15:41.700 --> 00:15:43.240
And Quart wasn't using that at first

00:15:43.500 --> 00:15:45.820
because it needed much more async things.

00:15:45.900 --> 00:15:52.259
But we've managed to develop a lot more things called--

00:15:52.280 --> 00:16:00.140
The term is called sans IO, like without input output, where we have all the behavior that's common to both.

00:16:00.200 --> 00:16:06.500
It doesn't require asyncio versus sync processes shared between CORT and Flask.

00:16:07.440 --> 00:16:10.960
